\strong{Part Two}

You notice a second question on the back of the homework assignment:

What is the largest magnitude you can get from adding only two of the
snailfish numbers?

Note that snailfish addition is not
\href{https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commutative_property}{commutative} - that
is, \code{x + y} and \code{y + x} can produce different results.

